{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Line a small loaf tin with cling film, leaving 10 cm overhanging on each side.","Place 85 g amaretti biscuits into mixing bowl and grind <nobr>Turbo\/2 sec\/3 times<\/nobr> until fine. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place cream in mixing bowl and, without measuring cup, whip <nobr>speed 3<\/nobr>, without setting a time, until soft peaks form, watching carefully to avoid over-whipping. Transfer to a bowl and set aside."," <strong>With butterfly whisk still in place<\/strong>, place eggs, egg yolks, sugar and Marsala in mixing bowl then cook <nobr>8 min\/80°C\/speed 3<\/nobr>. <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong> and transfer mixture to a large bowl then set aside to cool.","Once cooled, fold in reserved whipped cream with a metal spoon then fold in reserved crushed amaretti biscuits. Transfer to prepared loaf tin and cover with cling film before freezing overnight or for at least 8 hours.","To serve, use cling film to ease semifreddo out onto a serving plate (see tip). Break up remaining 15 g amaretti biscuits roughly by hand then scatter over the top, followed by the flaked almonds. Serve immediately cut in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["100 g amaretti biscuits","250 g whipping cream","3 medium eggs","3 egg yolks from medium eggs","60 g caster sugar","200 g Marsala","1 Tbsp flaked almonds"]}],"id":"r94186","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-3RBBTdMixlY\/XZanIcNrn0I\/AAAAAAAAg6k\/ur3dEub4L6QOe_ZBjcrvBKtXxzUy-8OjwCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_34UmxguXHhqJtOOB.png","title":"Semifreddo with Marsala and Amaretti","publishedAt":"2015-09-01T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"5.1 g","fat":"18.3 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"18.8 g","calories":"1088 kJ \/ 260 kcal"},"usefulItems":"1 lb loaf tin (16 x 11 x 7 cm), cling film, large bowl, serving plate, freezer","hintsAndTricks":["Place a serving plate in the freezer 30 minutes before you are 